Introduction

GOT7 is a seven-member boy group formed by JYP Entertainment. The group debuted on January 16, 2014, with their first mini album "Got It?" and quickly gained recognition for their dynamic performances and multinational lineup, which includes members from South Korea, Hong Kong, Thailand, and the United States.

Before their debut, JB and Jinyoung (formerly Junior) debuted as the duo JJ Project, while Jackson, Mark, Bambam, and Yugyeom appeared in the reality survival program WIN: Who Is Next.

In January 2021, GOT7's contract with JYP Entertainment expired, and all seven members chose not to renew, instead pursuing solo careers while affirming the group had not disbanded. On May 6, 2022, they introduced a new logo and launched official social media accounts under Warner Music Korea for future group promotions. GOT7 made their official comeback on May 23, 2022, with the self-titled EP "GOT7."
